    <node id="CONTENT_ID">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE</data>
      <data key="d1">The CONTENT_ID is an integer column that serves dual roles across related database tables. In the **content catalog** (a dimension table), it functions as a **surrogate primary key** that uniquely identifies each content item, ensuring efficient and stable referencing in the data warehouse. 

Simultaneously, in the **streams table** (a fact table), CONTENT_ID acts as a **foreign key** (with the alias `title_id`) linking streaming events to the corresponding entries in the content catalog. This establishes a critical relationship for analyzing content engagement, enabling joins between transactional streaming data and descriptive content metadata. 

The integer data type supports optimized storage and indexing for both key roles. No contradictions exist; the descriptions reflect contextual usage: as a unique identifier in the content dimension and as a reference in the streams fact table.</data>
      <data key="d2">6560620170abc6e57b18b7932d106d3f,cffcda8a51675f1f2fce635cc560a247</data>
      <data key="d3">ATTRIBUTE</data>
    </node>
